variables.name: PROTO_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The type of transport protocol (MMS or SMS). *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: MSG_ID
variables.comment:
* The ID of the message to be sent or downloaded. *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: MSG_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The type of the message to be sent or downloaded. * This field is only valid for MM. For SM, its value is always set to 0. *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: ERROR_TYPE
variables.comment:
* The type of the error code. *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: ERROR_CODE
variables.comment:
* The error code of sending/retrieving process. *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: RETRY_INDEX
variables.comment:
* How many times we tried to send or download the message. *

Type: INTEGER

variables.name: DUE_TIME
variables.comment:
* The time to do next retry. *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: LAST_TRY
variables.comment:
* The time we last tried to send or download the message. *

Type: INTEGER (long)

variables.name: SUBSCRIPTION_ID
variables.comment:
* The subscription to which the message belongs to. Its value will be * < 0 if the sub id cannot be determined. *

Type: INTEGER (long)
